WEBVTT

01:10.958 --> 01:11.791
Come in.

01:18.958 --> 01:24.000
A bank or some place gives a man a loan.

01:24.875 --> 01:28.041
Sometimes people can't pay the money back.

01:29.083 --> 01:31.666
You see they’re too poor.

01:32.291 --> 01:36.625
They have nothing valuable
for the bank to take.

01:37.041 --> 01:40.083
So the bank stops asking
and just writes it off.

01:40.750 --> 01:41.750
Just like that.

01:44.250 --> 01:46.833
They call it bad debt.

01:50.333 --> 01:51.291
So?

01:51.375 --> 01:52.750
What do you think?

01:55.333 --> 01:56.541
About?

02:02.250 --> 02:04.916
A drug dealer’s world is a cesspool.

02:05.000 --> 02:07.125
I don't like this idea, so I want to help you.

02:08.416 --> 02:09.250
So...

02:11.875 --> 02:14.500
Do you think...

02:14.583 --> 02:18.791
...it’s right for a man not to pay
his debts just 'cause he’s too poor?

02:19.750 --> 02:23.750
I hope you know what
you're doing with these gangsters.

02:24.041 --> 02:26.166
In any case...

02:26.250 --> 02:27.833
...the banks have all missed something.

02:34.666 --> 02:38.458
Ask the one-legged beggar what
his other leg is worth.

02:43.041 --> 02:44.041
Oh by the way...

02:45.083 --> 02:47.000
...what do you think of my new acquisition?

02:47.083 --> 02:49.958
Previous owner couldn't run it anymore.

02:50.250 --> 02:51.625
It's cool.

03:26.291 --> 03:27.625
What'd he say?

04:00.958 --> 04:03.958
Randal, are you going to
tell me what Emmie said?

04:07.375 --> 04:08.791
Uh Randal, listen...

04:10.166 --> 04:13.583
...we're good with picking locks.
Quick in and out.

04:15.333 --> 04:19.083
But doing drug deals using
a loan shark’s money is asking for trouble.

04:19.958 --> 04:21.250
Know what I mean?

04:24.625 --> 04:26.583
I need more than this Lester.

04:28.333 --> 04:30.541
Way more than this.

04:38.291 --> 04:39.375
What?

04:39.458 --> 04:41.291
Look it's simple.

04:41.375 --> 04:44.916
It's cash for the rocks.

04:45.000 --> 04:46.791
Then we repackage the
rocks and sell to make a profit.

04:46.875 --> 04:49.833
Emmie gets his money back and...

04:50.250 --> 04:51.625
...we make a big score.

04:51.875 --> 04:55.958
A bigger score than we've ever had.
More than a month of cracking locks.

04:57.041 --> 04:58.166
Two months.

04:58.250 --> 04:59.541
Ten months.

05:00.041 --> 05:00.958
Hey?

05:01.458 --> 05:02.458
Hello?

05:02.541 --> 05:03.375
Look at me.

05:03.458 --> 05:05.083
Just drive the car man.

05:15.875 --> 05:17.250
We'll be fine.

05:30.750 --> 05:34.500
Months Later

07:01.791 --> 07:04.333
Damn it Randal,
don’t people lose weight in the hospital?

07:08.541 --> 07:09.500
Damn.

07:12.166 --> 07:14.375
Hold on. Last three.

07:14.458 --> 07:18.041
One...two...three.

07:18.125 --> 07:19.958
Do you have him Pam?

07:21.500 --> 07:23.791
Slowly, slowly, slowly.

07:25.250 --> 07:26.458
One, two, three. Lift!

07:27.958 --> 07:28.958
Damn.

07:30.875 --> 07:32.083
Chill, let me help.

07:32.291 --> 07:33.250
I'll do that for you...

07:33.333 --> 07:34.250
Wait Warren.

07:35.083 --> 07:35.916
Okay.

07:44.250 --> 07:45.166
Okay.

07:45.250 --> 07:46.458
I've got it Pam.

07:50.458 --> 07:51.833
Which one?

07:52.458 --> 07:53.583
On the left.

07:53.666 --> 07:54.875
The door's open.

08:01.958 --> 08:03.500
Anyway. Are you okay?

08:03.583 --> 08:05.666
Yes. Thanks Warren.

08:05.833 --> 08:09.000
It's cool. But if you need help again,
let me know. I'll be here.

08:11.166 --> 08:12.000
I can come around again.

08:12.083 --> 08:14.458
You know you want to come around again.

09:28.666 --> 09:30.625
So what do you think?

09:36.041 --> 09:39.333
We're on the waiting list for
a place on the ground floor.

09:41.500 --> 09:43.541
But we were lucky to get this place...

09:45.291 --> 09:46.458
...for now.

09:50.500 --> 09:51.875
Pam.

09:56.000 --> 09:57.250
Thanks.

10:21.583 --> 10:24.041
Now, if you win this season
of Om-I-Wêreld then

10:24.125 --> 10:27.875
huge prizes are
coming your way!

10:27.958 --> 10:29.375
Hurry up.

10:31.125 --> 10:33.500
Hang on. Don't look yet.

10:34.166 --> 10:35.333
I'm not.

10:42.125 --> 10:44.041
Okay. You can look now.

10:50.750 --> 10:52.500
Welcome home babe.

10:55.125 --> 10:57.458
Remember when we were
kids and I broke my leg?

10:57.958 --> 10:58.958
Yes.

10:59.041 --> 11:01.166
You were such a tomboy...

11:01.250 --> 11:03.458
...always wanting to play soccer with the boys.

11:04.791 --> 11:06.375
I was so bored at home.

11:06.458 --> 11:08.625
My uncle didn't want to give
me my crutches back.

11:08.875 --> 11:11.500
You kept stealing them to smack the other kids.

11:17.958 --> 11:20.750
You spent everyday with me after that babe.

11:23.291 --> 11:26.250
Telling me stories of the world outside.

11:29.500 --> 11:34.291
That’s how I got through it
without pulling my hair out.

11:46.083 --> 11:47.625
What's this?

11:48.291 --> 11:50.958
Something to help you get through this time.

11:52.083 --> 11:53.000
Open it.

11:57.083 --> 11:58.333
What now?

11:58.750 --> 12:00.250
Take it back.

12:03.541 --> 12:05.000
Are you serious?

12:05.083 --> 12:06.583
Yes.

12:06.666 --> 12:08.500
We can't afford it. Take it back.

12:08.958 --> 12:10.416
You don't even know what it is.

12:10.500 --> 12:13.083
It doesn't matter.
We don't have money for this shit.

12:15.875 --> 12:18.583
Can’t we, just for one day,
forget that we don’t have money?

12:21.750 --> 12:23.291
What the hell!

12:24.541 --> 12:26.458
Have you seen my legs?

12:27.375 --> 12:28.291
Hey?

12:29.125 --> 12:30.250
Look at them!

12:30.958 --> 12:32.875
I can't do anything. I can't work.

12:33.125 --> 12:34.458
Look at them!

12:36.500 --> 12:38.291
Do you know how much crap we're in...

12:38.375 --> 12:39.875
...and you're wasting our money on -

12:39.958 --> 12:41.125
Stop it.

12:42.750 --> 12:45.458
What kind of trouble are we in Randal?

12:45.625 --> 12:47.541
What are you so afraid of?

12:57.375 --> 12:59.250
Open it, or don't.

13:00.250 --> 13:02.833
I just wanted to give you
something to do when I'm not around.

13:30.791 --> 13:32.458
Shit.

13:47.250 --> 13:49.000
They say we’re in a drought.

13:50.666 --> 13:53.333
The water will be back in a few days.

13:56.041 --> 13:58.250
I can't take care of you anymore.

14:15.333 --> 14:17.791
I've never asked that of you.

14:20.833 --> 14:22.583
We look after each other.

14:22.875 --> 14:24.125
Remember?

15:59.625 --> 16:01.083
What?

16:01.166 --> 16:02.666
Nothing.

16:21.625 --> 16:23.333
Leave it.

16:24.541 --> 16:26.625
Leave it. It's okay.

17:33.500 --> 17:35.500
And this?

17:52.041 --> 17:54.375
Asshole.

18:05.791 --> 18:06.958
Hello.

18:07.041 --> 18:08.458
Light it up baby girl.

18:11.625 --> 18:12.875
Hold on.

19:00.041 --> 19:01.541
Shit.

19:03.166 --> 19:04.208
Randal?

19:04.291 --> 19:05.458
Yeah...

19:06.041 --> 19:08.166
...I’ll be there now. Go back to sleep.

19:43.958 --> 19:45.666
And now?

19:47.250 --> 19:48.791
What's going on here?

22:09.166 --> 22:10.500
Rubbish.

23:10.250 --> 23:11.333
Pam?

23:34.958 --> 23:36.541
Who is it?

23:47.958 --> 23:49.083
Boo.

23:50.958 --> 23:52.750
May I come in?

24:43.833 --> 24:44.958
So?

24:48.125 --> 24:50.375
What’ve the doctors said about your legs?

24:52.791 --> 24:55.291
Nah, it’s uhm not good.

24:59.041 --> 25:00.583
Yeah...

25:01.250 --> 25:02.833
...gangsters.

25:03.666 --> 25:05.541
I warned you.

25:05.625 --> 25:09.333
You just can’t trust them, my friend.

25:12.166 --> 25:14.041
They talk about money...

25:14.125 --> 25:16.458
...but they deal in blood.

25:18.875 --> 25:22.666
At least you lived to tell the tale, huh?

25:23.958 --> 25:26.958
I mean, look at your friend, Lester.

25:34.958 --> 25:36.458
Sorry.

25:52.458 --> 25:55.000
So aren’t you going to
tell me what happened to you?

25:55.875 --> 25:57.958
That drug merchant...

26:09.583 --> 26:11.333
What's going on?

26:14.958 --> 26:17.291
You must be Pam?

26:24.375 --> 26:26.458
Oh yes and this is Faizel.

26:30.250 --> 26:31.875
Randal?

26:34.000 --> 26:36.291
Something wrong with your phone?

26:36.541 --> 26:39.291
Oh no, the network is messed up here.

26:43.875 --> 26:45.541
Look.

26:47.041 --> 26:48.291
Just one thing.

26:48.375 --> 26:49.833
I...

26:50.666 --> 26:52.708
...am a reasonable guy.

26:52.791 --> 26:54.458
Ask Faizel. Right?

26:55.333 --> 26:58.458
And I understand all of this crap...

26:58.541 --> 27:00.791
...that you are going through my brother.

27:07.250 --> 27:09.375
But a deal is a deal.

27:17.958 --> 27:20.000
Where's my money?

27:22.791 --> 27:24.458
Come on Emmie.

27:25.291 --> 27:27.333
We go way back.

27:28.541 --> 27:29.583
You know I'm good for it.

27:29.666 --> 27:31.291
I just need some time, that’s all.

27:43.625 --> 27:45.000
You.

27:52.083 --> 27:53.291
Bad debt.

27:53.375 --> 27:55.875
Remember that little chat?

28:01.333 --> 28:05.125
Even the one-legged beggar
can still lose his other leg.

28:17.750 --> 28:19.625
You've got seven days.

28:40.125 --> 28:41.625
Tell me.

28:42.166 --> 28:44.000
Don't worry about it.

28:44.541 --> 28:46.250
How much do you owe him?

28:46.791 --> 28:49.000
Twenty-five thousand.

28:49.958 --> 28:51.500
I’ll get it back.

28:54.541 --> 28:57.041
So Lester didn't die in a drive-by?

28:59.958 --> 29:02.791
It had to do with drug dealers?

29:09.375 --> 29:11.458
What the hell did you do Randal?

29:13.166 --> 29:15.791
I had a good deal Pam.

29:16.250 --> 29:19.916
I just needed Emmie's money
to make it work. That's all.

29:20.000 --> 29:22.458
We would've been sorted for life.

29:24.750 --> 29:27.750
Could’ve taken us out of this shit-hole.

29:29.000 --> 29:31.041
Aren’t you tired of living like this?

29:32.750 --> 29:34.666
So you borrowed money...

29:34.750 --> 29:36.458
...from a loan shark...

29:36.541 --> 29:38.583
...to pay drug dealers.

29:39.583 --> 29:42.083
And got Lester killed in the process.

29:43.000 --> 29:45.000
We have each other.

29:46.500 --> 29:48.250
What more do you want?

29:48.333 --> 29:49.166
There's...

29:49.250 --> 29:50.458
Shut up.

29:51.583 --> 29:53.250
I have...

29:53.333 --> 29:55.375
...tolerated enough from you Randal.

29:57.375 --> 30:01.958
I’ve never asked you to be
an angel but we had enough.

30:03.250 --> 30:05.625
What's so bad about our life hey?

30:07.333 --> 30:09.083
We have each other.

30:10.458 --> 30:12.333
What more do you need?

30:17.083 --> 30:18.958
Put ice on your face.

30:22.583 --> 30:23.791
What's up Brendan?

30:23.875 --> 30:24.958
Yeah it's Randal.

30:25.166 --> 30:26.666
What's up my brother from another mother.

30:27.000 --> 30:29.583
I heard you're back from the dead.

30:30.250 --> 30:31.666
Damn bro. You're like Jesus.

30:31.875 --> 30:34.666
Like that bird...uh what’s it called...

30:34.750 --> 30:35.833
...a phoenix.

30:37.333 --> 30:38.458
Yeah a phoenix.

30:39.250 --> 30:41.208
Check it, I'm uh looking for a bit of work.

30:41.291 --> 30:44.166
You know...credit cards...

30:44.250 --> 30:46.166
That’s right.

30:46.625 --> 30:48.458
Cool. So you'll let me know.

30:50.583 --> 30:52.541
Come on Yazid, you know I can work.

30:52.625 --> 30:53.750
My hands...

30:54.250 --> 30:55.916
What are you gonna do
when the police come for you?

30:56.000 --> 30:56.958
Roll away?

31:00.958 --> 31:02.125
Roll away.

31:54.875 --> 31:56.875
Oh you’re back.

32:16.041 --> 32:18.250
So you're all tight.

32:59.750 --> 33:01.375
Here's the money.

33:02.833 --> 33:03.958
Is that it?

33:55.083 --> 33:58.875
Ten triple one, emergency line.
How may I help you?

34:01.250 --> 34:02.500
Hello?

34:05.500 --> 34:06.750
Hello?

34:10.958 --> 34:12.250
Hello?

35:43.333 --> 35:44.833
Water’s back.

35:45.500 --> 35:47.125
It's nice and hot.

36:04.541 --> 36:06.083
Good.

36:06.666 --> 36:08.041
The bedroom's getting cold.

36:14.875 --> 36:17.750
I see there's guys in Warren's block.

36:18.125 --> 36:20.458
They drive a sick BMW.

36:24.791 --> 36:27.083
The main guy's name is Lawyer.

36:30.583 --> 36:32.333
Why?

36:35.291 --> 36:37.500
We should call the police.

36:37.583 --> 36:39.791
You should've done it yesterday.

36:39.875 --> 36:42.083
He keeps money in there.

36:42.166 --> 36:43.958
Probably...

36:44.750 --> 36:45.875
...a hundred thousand.

36:46.541 --> 36:48.125
Maybe more.

36:49.291 --> 36:51.583
That's more than enough
to get Emmie off our backs.

36:51.958 --> 36:53.500
Are you crazy?

36:54.875 --> 36:55.875
We're not doing this.

36:55.958 --> 36:57.083
I have a plan.

36:57.166 --> 36:58.750
Lester is dead because of your last plan!

37:09.666 --> 37:11.458
This guy's no joke Randal.

37:12.458 --> 37:14.458
For God's sake, he lives across the block!

37:15.750 --> 37:17.250
We're not doing this.

37:18.333 --> 37:19.750
Promise me.

37:23.750 --> 37:25.250
Promise me.

37:34.333 --> 37:36.166
I’m selling these binoculars.

38:09.833 --> 38:15.541
<i>Warren, supper 2night?</i>

38:35.250 --> 38:36.750
Pastor White?

38:37.250 --> 38:41.625
I went to visit Lester’s family a few days ago.

38:43.875 --> 38:46.166
They’re doing okay.

38:51.583 --> 38:54.958
I've known you and Lester since you were kids.

38:55.875 --> 38:58.166
When you used to steal from the offering plate.

39:03.250 --> 39:06.250
I hear you've been selling
all your stuff to save the church.

39:08.458 --> 39:10.375
Yes. I wait on the Lord.

39:11.958 --> 39:14.250
He will provide.

39:21.958 --> 39:26.250
They build piles of shit
and tell us to live in it.

39:28.083 --> 39:30.375
Then they wonder why it stinks so badly.

39:33.166 --> 39:35.000
You see Pastor...

39:36.000 --> 39:37.625
I want to get out of here.

39:38.166 --> 39:40.250
Anyway that I can.

39:42.291 --> 39:47.333
So forgive me if I leave the
waiting for the Lord to you.

39:49.333 --> 39:51.625
He can catch up with
me when He feels like it.

39:52.583 --> 39:55.291
That's if He gives a shit.

40:05.750 --> 40:07.166
You know Randal...

40:07.958 --> 40:09.333
I'm praying for you.

40:12.333 --> 40:14.375
I know you're in trouble.

40:14.958 --> 40:16.458
But have faith.

40:18.291 --> 40:21.958
The Israelites eventually
made it to the promised land.

40:24.583 --> 40:26.333
<i>For sure :-)</i>

40:26.458 --> 40:27.958
Yeah...

40:28.666 --> 40:31.291
And Moses was dead before they got there.

41:02.625 --> 41:05.458
You're at the wrong place lady.

41:21.583 --> 41:24.166
Now you're at the right place.

41:38.625 --> 41:41.250
You're lying, you rubbish.

42:50.291 --> 42:51.375
There you go.

42:58.250 --> 42:59.166
Two.

42:59.833 --> 43:00.666
I'm watching you.

43:00.750 --> 43:01.958
Keep watching.

43:02.708 --> 43:03.541
Three.

43:04.250 --> 43:05.541
Double four.

43:05.958 --> 43:07.083
Two fives.

43:09.250 --> 43:10.375
Bullshit.

43:10.458 --> 43:11.458
Check it out.

43:13.375 --> 43:14.250
Damn it.

43:14.458 --> 43:15.541
Pick up.

43:15.625 --> 43:16.791
- Give me a break. Please I'm begging you.

43:16.875 --> 43:20.166
- Give me a break. Please I'm begging you.
- What break? What do you think this is?

43:20.458 --> 43:21.958
Down it.

43:26.958 --> 43:28.250
One more.

43:32.666 --> 43:33.625
Warren.

43:34.166 --> 43:37.458
Some of us have to work tomorrow so...

43:38.541 --> 43:39.375
...piss off.

43:39.458 --> 43:41.958
Leave the dishes, I’ll sort them out.

43:45.666 --> 43:46.875
Okay.

43:51.958 --> 43:52.875
Night.

43:52.958 --> 43:53.958
Goodnight.

43:59.083 --> 44:02.000
Warren you should come chill
here with me more.

44:02.083 --> 44:04.083
We can play cards. Get drunk.

44:04.166 --> 44:05.750
And you can lose.

44:08.000 --> 44:10.250
You miss him?

44:12.583 --> 44:14.250
Lester.

44:15.833 --> 44:16.958
Yes.

44:19.291 --> 44:20.750
Me too.

44:25.500 --> 44:27.041
Come I want to show you something.

44:27.625 --> 44:28.958
I can't see anything.

44:29.291 --> 44:31.666
Hello. Turn the knob man.

44:37.750 --> 44:39.375
There's Lawyer.

44:39.666 --> 44:41.291
Asshole.

44:42.458 --> 44:44.791
A woman came to your place today.

44:44.875 --> 44:46.666
She showed you a picture.

44:47.250 --> 44:49.333
Oh yes. Some missing cop.

44:51.791 --> 44:53.791
He's not missing.

44:55.125 --> 44:56.458
He's dead.

45:03.625 --> 45:05.291
And you saw it.

45:05.958 --> 45:07.583
So you called the cops?

45:08.000 --> 45:10.375
Is that why that detective is sniffing around?

45:11.083 --> 45:12.541
They were smuggling something.

45:13.250 --> 45:16.250
There's probably a hundred
thousand in cash over there.

45:16.583 --> 45:18.958
That Lawyer-guy, or whatever his name is...

45:19.750 --> 45:20.666
He kept it all.

45:20.750 --> 45:22.250
No way Randal!

45:23.041 --> 45:24.458
That's madness!

45:24.541 --> 45:26.250
Why do you want to fuck
around with a guy like that?

45:27.958 --> 45:30.333
Do you know that him and Spook
killed a kid last week?

45:30.875 --> 45:31.708
Who?

45:31.791 --> 45:32.875
Spook, man.

45:33.458 --> 45:35.791
That albino-guy that's always with him.

45:38.166 --> 45:39.583
Okay so...

45:39.666 --> 45:42.041
...this kid was selling on Lawyer's turf.

45:42.666 --> 45:44.625
But nothing big - small scale.

45:46.625 --> 45:49.000
So he's playing soccer with his friends...

45:50.458 --> 45:52.833
...when the BMW comes
speeding round the corner. Really fast.

45:53.000 --> 45:55.375
They run down the kid...

45:57.625 --> 46:00.000
They run down the kid in front of everyone.

46:04.333 --> 46:06.375
He gets out the car.
Walks up to the kid's mom...

46:06.458 --> 46:07.875
...and says it was an accident.

46:09.458 --> 46:11.041
A little kid.

46:13.750 --> 46:16.083
Why would you want to
steal from a guy like that?

46:18.458 --> 46:21.541
To tell you the truth Warren,
I don't have a choice.

46:24.041 --> 46:26.458
If I don't have the money by Tuesday...

46:28.666 --> 46:30.750
...Pam and I are done for.

46:42.166 --> 46:43.791
How are we going to get it?

46:45.666 --> 46:48.041
I’ll ask him nicely.

46:48.958 --> 46:50.166
Do you have his number?

46:55.250 --> 46:56.250
Put the number on private.

46:56.333 --> 46:57.916
Warren, I swear if you don't shut...

46:58.000 --> 46:59.000
Hello.

47:00.541 --> 47:01.666
Lawyer?

47:02.083 --> 47:03.333
Who's this?

47:03.958 --> 47:05.583
I know what you did to that cop.

47:05.666 --> 47:07.500
Is this a joke?

47:10.166 --> 47:12.083
Do you know who you're dealing with here?

47:12.166 --> 47:13.583
Who are you?

47:15.625 --> 47:16.875
A friend.

47:17.125 --> 47:18.666
I know about the money too.

47:19.000 --> 47:22.583
I'm phoning to warn you
before I call the cops.

47:24.333 --> 47:25.541
But...

47:26.458 --> 47:28.500
